snippet.textDisplay: Have you ever heard the Harry Potter: Chamber of Secrets soundtrack? A questionably good game (I think it's an okay Zelda clone when it isn't broken) but it's perhaps Soule's greatest work ever, with the Diagon Alley theme (the PC vs. Console vs. of course Handheld versions are all different, with even the mostly same console versions having minor changes, the GBA game being so bad a game reviewer called The Completionist says it'll be the last game he reviews) is one of the most melancholy and beautifully nostalgiac songs I've ever heard, and on PC it's the menu theme, though I feel being able to return to a song like that that evokes feelings of longing for the past at any point diminishes it somewhat. Still, you have superb taste as always. This is good shit.
snippet.textOriginal: Have you ever heard the Harry Potter: Chamber of Secrets soundtrack?
